.SH NAME
CSSNestedDeclarations \- CSSNestedDeclarations
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]CSSNestedDeclarations\f[B]\f[R] interface of the CSS Rule
API is used to group nested \f[CR]CSSRule\f[R]s.
.PP
The interface allows the CSS Object Model (CSSOM to mirror the structure
of CSS documents with nested CSS rules, and ensure that rules are parsed
and evaluated in the order that they are declared.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] > Browser versions with implementations that do not
support this interface may parse nested rules in the wrong order.
.RE
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
\f[I]Inherits properties from its ancestor \f[CI]CSSRule\f[I].\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]CSSNestedDeclarations.style\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns the values of the nested rules.
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
\f[I]No specific methods; inherits methods from its ancestor
\f[CI]CSSRule\f[I].\f[R]
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS CSS
The CSS below includes a selector \f[CR].foo\f[R] that contains two
declarations and a media query.
.IP
.EX
\&.foo {
  \f[B]background\-color\f[R]: silver;
  \f[B]\[at]media\f[R] (screen) {
    color\f[BI]:\f[R] tomato;
  }
  \f[B]color\f[R]: black;
}
.EE
.PP
This is represented by a number of JavaScript objects in the CSS Object
Model:
.IP \[bu] 2
A \f[CR]CSSStyleRule\f[R] object that represents the
\f[CR]background\-color: silver\f[R] rule.
This can be returned via \f[CR]document.styleSheets[0].cssRules[0]\f[R].
.IP \[bu] 2
A \f[CR]CSSMediaRule\f[R] object that represents the
\f[CR]\[at]media (screen)\f[R] rule, and which can be returned via
\f[CR]document.styleSheets[0].cssRules[0].cssRules[0]\f[R].
.RS 2
.IP \[bu] 2
The \f[CR]CSSMediaRule\f[R] object contains a
\f[CR]CSSNestedDeclaration\f[R] object which represents the
\f[CR]color: tomato\f[R] rule nested by the
\f[CR]\[at]media (screen)\f[R] rule.
This can be returned via
\f[CR]document.styleSheets[0].cssRules[0].cssRules[0].cssRules[0]\f[R].
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
The final rule is a \f[CR]CSSNestedDeclaration\f[R] object that
represents the \f[CR]color: black\f[R] rule in the stylesheet, and which
can be returned via
\f[CR]document.styleSheets[0].cssRules[0].cssRules[1]\f[R].
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] All top\-level styles after the first
\f[CR]CSSNestedDeclaration\f[R] must also be represented as
\f[CR]CSSNestedDeclaration\f[R] objects in order to follow the CSS
nested declarations rule
.RE
.SS CSSOM (CSS Object Model)
.IP
.EX
↳ CSSStyleRule
  .style
    \- background\-color: silver
  ↳ CSSMediaRule
    ↳ CSSNestedDeclarations
      .style (CSSStyleDeclaration, 1) =
      \- color: tomato
  ↳ CSSNestedDeclarations
    .style (CSSStyleDeclaration, 1) =
      \- color: black
.EE
